Melania and Donald Trump released a statement during Down Syndrome Awareness Month, expressing their support for individuals with Down syndrome. They emphasized the importance of understanding the condition and ensuring that those with Down syndrome can fully participate in society. They also mentioned the advancements in research and treatment that have led to healthier and longer lives for individuals with Down syndrome. They highlighted the need for education and acceptance, as well as the importance of respecting the dignity and rights of all individuals. The Trump administration pledged to continue creating opportunities and supporting individuals with Down syndrome.